{"article_id":"F59qqEnElp7ODGp5","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The American public is now evenly split in its opinion of the Affordable Care Act , an improvement in the law 's standing ,","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"according to a new /TIPP poll .","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"Some 47 percent of American adults support the law","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"known as Obamacare ,","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"and 47 percent are opposed ,","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"finds the poll ,","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"conducted between April 26 and May 1 .","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"This result is just one indicator","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"- and a tentative one -","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"that","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"when the Obamacare marketplaces outperformed expectations","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"by exceeding 7 million people enrolled ,","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"the news may have given Obamacare a boost in public opinion .","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"So far , other recent polls still find","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"that more people disapprove of the law","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"than approve ,","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"and that public opinion is little changed since the April 1 enrollment deadline .","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"When the Monitor/TIPP poll asked in a late March survey","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"whether people support or oppose the health-care law","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"passed in 2010 ,","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"more than half were opposed","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"( 51 percent )","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"and 40 percent said","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"they support the law .","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"So the even split between the \" support \" and \" oppose \" camps , in the new poll , looks like a considerable change since March .","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"\" They are in a statistical dead heat , \"","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"says pollster Raghavan Mayur , president of TechnoMetrica Market Intelligence , by e-mail .","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"The margin of error , an estimate","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"of how much the poll results may differ from actual public opinion ,","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"is 3.4 percentage points , similar to other national polling on the subject .","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"Although the margin of error makes poll results a bit fuzzy ,","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"Mr. Mayur says","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"support for the law \" has increased \" since late March .","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"With other polls not seeing that trend ,","depth":5},{"id":34,"text":"what remains to be seen is whether the Monitor/TIPP result is a temporary outlier or an early sign","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"that views toward the law are becoming a bit more positive .","depth":6},{"id":36,"text":"Public opinion about the law is important","depth":4},{"id":37,"text":"because health-care policy promises to remain an issue of heated political debate .","depth":5},{"id":38,"text":"Republicans are hoping to leverage opposition to the law in their favor in congressional elections ,","depth":6},{"id":39,"text":"while Democrats are hoping","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"their support of the law won ' t be too much of a liability .","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"This year marks the law ' s major rollout phase , with \" exchanges , \" or marketplaces ,","depth":5},{"id":42,"text":"including the federal HealthCare.gov website","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"launching for individuals to shop for coverage","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"that complies with the law .","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"Even an improved public view of the law isn ' t a rosy one .","depth":6},{"id":46,"text":"In the Monitor/TIPP poll , fully 44 percent of respondents say","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"Congress should repeal the law .","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"One of the act ' s less-popular provisions is the \" individual mandate , \"","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"which calls on people to buy insurance this year","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"( if they don ' t have it already )","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"or face a possible tax penalty .","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"The high cost of health care remains a public concern","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"( as it was before the law ) ,","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"and many Americans worry about having limited access to particular doctors and care providers under the health plans","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"available on the Obamacare exchanges .","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"Other elements of the law are popular , such as a provision","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"to ensure","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"that people can obtain insurance","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"regardless of preexisting medical conditions .","depth":12},{"id":60,"text":"When the White House reported","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"that the number of people","depth":13},{"id":62,"text":"applying for insurance on the exchanges","depth":13},{"id":63,"text":"surged to 8 million as of early April ,","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"President Obama sought to use the news","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"to galvanize public support .","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"\" Independent experts now estimate","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"that millions of Americans","depth":15},{"id":68,"text":"who were uninsured","depth":15},{"id":69,"text":"have gained coverage this year","depth":14},{"id":70,"text":"- with millions more to come next year and the year after , \"","depth":13},{"id":71,"text":"Mr. Obama said on April 17 .","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"\" This thing is working . \"","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"Pollsters ,","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"in framing their survey questions about the ACA ,","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"characterize it as a `` health reform law '' or a `` law","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"making changes to the health-care system . ''","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"( The Monitor/TIPP poll calls it the `` health care law","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"passed in 2010 ,","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"also known as Obamacare . '' )","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"For comparison , here is the mix of late-April poll results","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"regarding Obamacare","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"( as tracked by the website PollingReport.com ) ,","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"presented in chronological order from the most recent poll to one","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"that concluded on April 21 .","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"36 percent say","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"law is a \" good idea \"","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"( up from 35 percent in March )","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"46 percent say","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"\" bad idea \"","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"( down from 49 percent in March )","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"Get the Monitor Stories","depth":4},{"id":92,"text":"you care about","depth":4},{"id":93,"text":"delivered to your inbox .","depth":3},{"id":94,"text":"By signing up ,","depth":3},{"id":95,"text":"you agree to our Privacy Policy","depth":3}],"relations":[{"parent":191,"left":186,"right":190,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":186,"left":131,"right":185,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":131,"left":102,"right":130,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":102,"left":97,"right":101,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":97,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":101,"left":99,"right":100,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":99,"left":98,"right":4,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":98,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":100,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":130,"left":127,"right":129,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":127,"left":119,"right":126,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":119,"left":107,"right":118,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":107,"l